Hello all,

I was hoping someone could help us with fixing our visual issue.

#### What are you trying to do?
We have a grid based screen, for example 8x6 cells.
While dragging we want to switch positions from the dragged from and dropped to position.

Example:
1.2 = (row 1 column 2)
2.3 = (row 2 column 3)

If we drag 1.2 to 2.3, all items in row 2 after column 3 are shifted to the right. After a drop detected with (cdkDropListDropped) on the cdkDropList element, we detect if the item is dropped inside the current row, or a new row.
Then we use either moveItemInArray or transferArrayItem to recreate the arrays. 

The problem with this, is while you are dragging, the items move to the right. This causes the grid (normally 6 width) to be 7 width for a moment. We want to prevent this. 

If we use cdkDropListExited and cdkDropListEntered, we can see which item is being dragged to where and remove an item from the array. This doesn't work, as it stops dragging while changing the array. This makes us only able to move an item to 1 row below or above at a time.

So we don't want the default behaviour where you move an item to another array, but we want to "trade" items, where they replace eachother. The trading is already arranged after dropping, but we want the user to feel the same way while dragging the item.

Thanks in advance for your help!

